Welcome
The Airports Commission, City and County
of San Francisco, operates San Francisco
International Airport as a public service enterprise
for residents and visitors in the Greater San
Francisco Bay Area and Northern California, as
well as for travelers between the continental
United States and all other points of the globe.
San Francisco International is served by 35
air carriers with service ranging from the local Bay
Area to worldwide passenger and cargo lines on
international routes.
San Francisco International is well under way
with a $500 million program of improvement and
development. When construction is complete, San
Francisco will boast one of the most compact,
convenient and up-to-date airports in the world.
Welcome to San Francisco International—
America's west coast air gateway to the world.
